<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_527a4f78-b94d-47ef-a36e-de5dcee74c6d" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>7.1.1</sptc><title id="_5e544ff0-e89c-432d-8410-3a27a69652b9">Scope</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_db1b55c9-9c74-41d3-ba9e-5e194878ec95" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_8c302233-eead-4737-8537-3bdff72e36d2">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>This Section sets out the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1236_1.0.0.xml#_2f02788f-8757-4689-b36e-e44d96524cc9" id="_e2afadb8-81f9-4ddf-ba8a-3fa382a99de3" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Deemed-to-Satisfy Provisions</xref> for—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_46255a6e-2eff-4bbe-8257-707319776d6b">metal sheet roofing (see <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4204_0.3.0.xml#_ded59f17-2977-4a78-8b93-3a81ec6e1222" id="_134829f7-a064-4f60-b144-926d8e2cd97d" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 7.2</xref>); and</li><li id="_bd178178-927c-49c3-a725-ec9f6f42cd8a">roof tiles (see <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4205_0.3.0.xml#_9fbc441b-1616-4781-bab4-59bee869a95f" id="_5856ab08-45ce-4d0c-87bf-2f24443c35cc" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 7.3</xref>); and</li><li id="_55cd2885-b8b9-4c81-9fb8-41ecf88c8d86">gutters and downpipes (see <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4206_0.8.0.xml#_1c715f7d-5c3a-432b-a4e6-08c8b0d54b10" id="_1d86e3bd-bfec-41b4-ab8f-25e4d8b6d3f9" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 7.4</xref>); and</li><li id="_5d251caf-661a-430a-8bbb-c2f9e3686e2e">timber and composite wall cladding (see <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4207_0.4.0.xml#_d2cf2638-e02b-44b1-af2b-6fcd70502fd3" id="_396c314c-9b21-439f-b393-bc5f0d8265ee" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 7.5</xref>).</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_27ff8695-f07d-4854-a1e6-8894467e8a31" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_848e70a2-e371-4e33-9312-51e7752d8e09">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>For other roof and wall cladding provisions not included in this Section, refer to NCC Volume Two <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1810#_09cf0558-d4b2-446a-9578-8248581eafac" id="_87bc2615-3e56-46b4-a44b-4fa0108946c9" publishing-id="vol2" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">H1D7(5)</xref> Metal wall cladding.</p></subclause><callout id="_6435be1a-fbbf-4ab9-8bce-d4ffc85fd7d6"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>This Part contains requirements including weatherproofing and structural requirements, for wall and roof systems. Gutter and downpipe requirements are also contained in this Part.</p><p>It should be noted that other construction methods may be used to achieve the same results as specified in this Part provided they comply with the appropriate <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1395_4.0.0.xml#_f7304862-3529-49d7-9f62-352bcbcb6294" id="_8bd8be01-55ff-402a-b0bc-5b3881139f9e" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Requirements</xref>.</p></callout></clause>